<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-10-15T17:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-07-28T18:00:00-05:00" n="194" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d194">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">C.P.(Gen)Doc.1.J.17.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="smallcaps">Article 74 bis</hi></head>
                        <dateline>
                            <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-outside-research" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1946-10-15T23:59:59+01:00" notBefore="1946-07-29T00:00:00+01:00">undated</date>
                        </dateline>
                        <p>Insert the following in the financial clauses of the Peace Treaty with
                            Italy: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p><hi rend="italic">Article</hi> … “Italy shall undertake to pay in
                                    gold to the Bank of Greece within three months of the coming
                                    into force of the present Treaty the sum of 64,800,000 dollars
                                    (1938 value), to which the advances <pb facs="0718" n="706" xml:id="pg_706"/> made by the Bank of Greece to the Italian
                                    occupation authorities amount, in addition to the occupation
                                    expenses borne by Greece under the agreement of March 14, 1942,
                                    between the German and Italian Governments, and all subsequent
                                    modifications thereto.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>